    "role": "arzt",
    "content": "I see, thank you for those details. It\u2019s important to have a clear timeline and understanding of your symptoms. Two weeks is a significant period, and the fact that you\u2019re experiencing shortness of breath both at night and during physical activity is concerning.\n\nLet\u2019s think about this like a puzzle. The elevated blood pressure and faster pulse, along with the shortness of breath and chest tightness, could point to a few different things. One possibility is that your body is working harder to get enough oxygen, which can happen if there\u2019s an issue with your lungs or heart. Another thought is that it might be related to something like anxiety or stress, which can also cause these symptoms.\n\nTo help narrow it down, I\u2019d like to ask a few more questions. Have you noticed any swelling in your legs or ankles? Sometimes fluid retention can be a sign of heart issues. \n\nAlso, do you have any history of allergies or asthma? Even if you haven\u2019t had them before, they can develop later in life.\n\nAnd, how about your energy levels? Are you feeling more tired than usual, even when you\u2019re not being physically active?\n\nLastly, have you had any recent colds, flu, or infections? Sometimes respiratory issues can linger after an infection and cause ongoing symptoms.\n\nWe\u2019ll take this one step at a time, and I\u2019ll make sure we get to the bottom of it."
